      <h2 class="program-title-lg mb-4">Accelerating V2X Cohort</h2>
      <p class="program-text">
        The Accelerating V2X Cohort is a collaborative initiative by the
        Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS) Joint Program Office (JPO) to
        support public agencies and other infrastructure owners and operators
        (IOOs) in accelerating the deployment of interoperable
        vehicle-to-everything (V2X) technologies. These technologies are
        critical to creating a modern, world-class transportation system that
        improves safety, efficiency, and reliability through seamless wireless
        connectivity among vehicles, mobile devices, and smart infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p class="program-text">
        The cohort is designed to accelerate the deployment of V2X technologies
        by fostering a community of practice among V2X deployers. Participating
        public entities have the opportunity to share their experiences,
        challenges, and best practices in planning and deploying V2X
        technologies.
      </p>
      <p class="program-text">
        Through monthly virtual meetings, cohort members come together to
        discuss emerging topics and to collaborate on addressing technical
        questions to support the successful, interoperable deployment of
        connected transportation technologies. USDOT provides facilitation,
        technical support, and access to resources to assist participants in
        achieving their project objectives.
      </p>
      <p class="program-text">
        If your agency is interested in joining or has any questions, please
        contact the ITS PCB Program at <Link
          href="mailto:itspcb@dot.gov"
          isExternal>itspcb@dot.gov</Link
        >.
      </p>
    </ProgramSection>
